This memorandum, issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., delegates authority to various government officials to submit cost estimates required by sections 102 and 106 of the CHIPS Act of 2022. The Secretary of Commerce is delegated the authority to submit cost estimates to Congress as required by sections 102(a)(4)(A)(i) and 106(c)(1)(A) of the Act. The Secretary of Defense is delegated the authority to submit the cost estimate required by section 102(b)(3)(A)(i) of the Act. The Secretary of State is delegated the authority to submit the cost estimate required by section 102(c)(3)(A)(i) of the Act. Lastly, the Director of the National Science Foundation is delegated the authority to submit the cost estimate required by section 102(d)(3)(A)(i) of the Act. The Secretary of Commerce is also directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.